{
  "texts": [
    "The Kullback-Leibler divergence is well established to be non-negative.",
    "Rearranging, we get",
    "The term on the left above is the cross-entropy loss of the LLM on the training corpus.",
    "The first term on the right converges to the inherent entropy of the natural language on the training corpus.",
    "During the training process, the parameters of the LLM are iteratively adjusted to minimize the cross-entropy."
  ]
}